cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper focuses on collective decision making, which involves multiple agents interacting with each other. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also discusses the impact of social network structure on decision making, which falls under the category of cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The use of agent-based simulations suggests a focus on cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper's emphasis on decision making and utility values suggests a possible fit with cs.SI (Social and Information Systems).
